The catch block in /(app)/+layout.ts uses a fragile duck-type check to re-throw SvelteKit redirect objects:
```typescript
if (e instanceof Response || (e as { status?: number })?.status) throw e;
```
SvelteKit's redirect() does NOT throw a Response — it throws a Redirect object. The instanceof Response check is always false. The code works only accidentally via the duck-typed .status check. This will also accidentally re-throw any error object that has a numeric status property.

## Severity
P2 IMPORTANT — Currently functional by accident; breaks under edge cases and misleads maintainers.

## Location
cognitest/frontend/src/routes/(app)/+layout.ts lines 19-22

## Fix
```typescript
import { redirect, isRedirect } from '@sveltejs/kit';
// ...
} catch (e) {
    if (isRedirect(e)) throw e;
    // Network error — let it through
}
```

