{"id":"medsimples-0ekz.19","title":"Fix: dashboard sessions list not refreshed after OrderTestModal creates a session","description":"## Issue

After OrderTestModal successfully creates a session and closes, the Recent Sessions card (Card 2) still shows the old list. There is no loadDashboard() call or state refresh triggered on modal close. The user must manually reload the page to see the new session.

```svelte
<OrderTestModal
    {testDefs}
    on:close={() => (showOrderModal = false)}
/>
```

The close handler only hides the modal, never refreshes data.

## Fix
Track whether a session was created in the modal, and refresh on close:
```svelte
on:close={(e) => {
    showOrderModal = false;
    if (e.detail?.sessionCreated) loadDashboard();
}}
```
The modal should dispatch close with { sessionCreated: true } on the success step.

## Severity
P3 — UX issue; data is stale but not wrong.

