   - Props: `entityType: 'org' | 'doctor'`, `entityId: number`, `canEdit: boolean`
   - Shows: current logo (from GET endpoint) or placeholder
   - When `canEdit`: file button, error state, "Remover logo" option

2. Add to `OrganizationDetail.tsx` or `OrganizationForm.tsx`:
   - Visible only to admins (check from auth context)
   - `<LogoUpload entityType="org" entityId={org.id} canEdit={isAdmin} />`

3. Add to `ProfileSettings.tsx`:
   - `<LogoUpload entityType="doctor" entityId={doctor.id} canEdit={true} />`

## Testing

- [ ] Upload PNG → preview shown, logo saved, display updates with cache-bust
- [ ] Upload JPEG → accepted (backend converts)
- [ ] Upload file > 2 MB → client-side error in Portuguese before any network request
- [ ] Upload invalid type → error shown before any network request
- [ ] Button disabled during upload, re-enabled after
- [ ] Button text shows "Enviando..." during upload
- [ ] Remove logo → placeholder shown, DB cleared
- [ ] Page reload → logo persists (fetched from GET endpoint)
- [ ] Non-admin → upload controls not visible (`canEdit=false`)
- [ ] Upload while offline → error shown in Portuguese

## Validation

- [ ] No canvas resize code (server handles it)
- [ ] No drag-and-drop code
- [ ] No LinearProgress component
- [ ] Preview updates on file select, clears after successful upload
- [ ] `bun run lint` and `bun run tsc --noEmit` pass
